FL,414,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F413A1773843068
OL,3,CAuthor Michael Rosen urges people to
OL,4,C'look everywhere' for meningitis rash
OL,6,FRosen said: "The rash, look everywhere
OL,7,Fif there's any doubt whatsoever, look
OL,8,Feverywhere.
OL,10,F"Don't be intrusive, obviously, but
OL,11,Farmpits, not so intrusive, ask your
OL,12,Fteenagers to look at their groin, and
OL,13,Fthe glass test is effective, it's
OL,14,Fabsolutely effective."
OL,16,FThe glass test is a way of checking
OL,17,Fwhether a rash is meningitis or not,
OL,18,Fby firmly pressing a glass against a
OL,19,Fskin rash, if it does not fade or
OL,20,Fdisappear, then people are urged by
OL,21,Fthe NHS to call 999.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,414,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F413A1773843068
OL,3,CAuthor Michael Rosen urges people to
OL,4,C'look everywhere' for meningitis rash
OL,6,FSpeaking about his son catching the
OL,7,Finfection, Rosen added: "It looked
OL,8,Flike flu, and people talk about the
OL,9,Frash and assume it's visible, that
OL,10,Fit's on your arms or on your chest.
OL,12,F"But I only found out when Eddie had
OL,13,Fdied, that the rash, the only place it
OL,14,Fappeared was in his armpits.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,414,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F413A1773843068
OL,3,CAuthor Michael Rosen urges people to
OL,4,C'look everywhere' for meningitis rash
OL,6,F"So by and large, you don't, when
OL,7,Fsomebody's ill, say, 'let me look at
OL,8,Fyour armpits', and with teenagers, you
OL,9,Fdon't say, 'let me look in your
OL,10,Fgroin', obviously, because it's a
OL,11,Fprivate matter, but it can also appear
OL,12,Fon the soles of your feet."
OL,14,FThe Harrow-born writer went on to say
OL,15,Fthat when Eddie, 18, was feeling
OL,16,Funwell, he "put him to bed, taking
OL,17,Fibuprofen and paracetamol, and he was
OL,18,Fdead in the morning".
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,414,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F413A1773843068
OL,3,CAuthor Michael Rosen urges people to
OL,4,C'look everywhere' for meningitis rash
OL,6,FHe said: "I mean, it really was that
OL,7,Fquick, and if I dare, I say simple,
OL,8,Fthat I went in, in the morning, and he
OL,9,Fwas lying on his back.
OL,11,F"I said, 'Eddie, I've got to go to
OL,12,Fwork now, Eddie', he didn't reply, and
OL,13,Fthen I felt him and then immediately
OL,14,Frealised he was dead.
OL,16,F"Hoping that he wasn't, (I) rang for
OL,17,Fthe ambulance guys to come over, they
OL,18,Ftold me to pull him out of the bed,
OL,19,Fand he had rigor mortis by then.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,414,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F413A1773843068
OL,3,CAuthor Michael Rosen urges people to
OL,4,C'look everywhere' for meningitis rash
OL,6,F"His arm was in the air, I pulled him
OL,7,Fonto the floor, some fluid came out of
OL,8,Fhis mouth, and then the ambulance guys
OL,9,Farrived about four or five minutes
OL,10,Flater, immediately said he's dead,
OL,11,Fthat was that (it) was really all that
OL,12,Fabrupt and terrifying."
OL,14,FRosen described Eddie's death as
OL,15,F"abrupt and terrifying", but added he
OL,16,Flikes to think Eddie was a
OL,17,F"contributing factor" for people
OL,18,Fgetting the MenC vaccine, which fights
OL,19,Fthe C variant of meningitis, as it
OL,20,Fcame in, in 1999, the year he died.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,414,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41307
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F413A1773843068
OL,3,CAuthor Michael Rosen urges people to
OL,4,C'look everywhere' for meningitis rash
OL,6,FFollowing the recent outbreak, GPs
OL,7,Facross the country have now been told
OL,8,Fto prescribe antibiotics to anyone who
OL,9,Fvisited a nightclub in Canterbury from
OL,10,FMarch 5-7, plus students from the
OL,11,FUniversity of Kent.
OL,13,FThe NHS says meningitis is an
OL,14,Finfection of the protective membranes
OL,15,Fthat surround the brain and spinal
OL,16,Fcord (meninges).
OL,18,FIt says the infection is most common
OL,19,Fin babies, young children, teenagers,
OL,20,Fand young adults, and can be very
OL,21,Fserious if not treated quickly.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/8
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
